{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Lathe",
  "description": "MESH_DEFORM_AND_CURVE_GEOMETRY_DESIGN P3 demo — node.revolve_curve seam render. A wavy vase profile (node.range -> node.array_math sine wobble -> node.combine_xy) is revolved a full sweep (node.revolve_curve, sweep=2*pi, the default) and triangulated (node.make_triangles). At sweep=2*pi the seam column's positions coincide exactly with column 0, so the seam is a lighting-continuity check: the finite-difference normals node.make_triangles computes must agree across the seam with no visible crack, because the seam vertices share position AND the grid wraps cleanly (D5's seam-duplication contract).",
  "presetMetadata": {
    "id": "Lathe",
    "displayName": "Lathe",
    "category": "Geometry",
    "oscPrefix": "lathe",
    "available": true,
    "isLineBased": false,
